The Ruger GP-100 revolver was first introduced in 1985 as a 2nd-generation of the Ruger Double Action revolvers, with intent to replace successful Ruger Security / Service / Speed Six line of revolvers. The GP-100 was a serious improvement over previous Ruger guns. It was made even stronger, with intent to fire an unlimited number of full-power .357 Magnum rounds, and was produced in many variations, with three basic barrel lengths (3" / 76 mm, 4" / 102 mm or 6" / 152 mm), various barrel profiles, with fixed or adjustable sights etc. GP-100 revolvers also are offered in two finish/material variations - blued carbon steel or polished stainless steel. Like most other Ruger guns, GP-100 revolvers are exceptionally strong, reliable and durable, and are great self-defense, security or practice weapons.
The Ruger GP-100 revolvers are double-action guns with exposed hammers and swing-out cylinders.

Hey all, I'm getting out of .308, as I'm not reloading, and ammo is hella expensive compared to .223, which is what I'm into more.

I have here a complete optics ready Hogan (Same as POF, used to be the same company) H308.  Gas Piston powered rifle with 16 inch barrel, full rail, 4.5 pound in house trigger with KNS pins.  More information can be found here: 

http://www.hoganguns.com

Breakdown of prices:
Rife - MSRP $2600.00 - new
12 PMAGS - $20.00 new
Magpul CTR with Larue RISR - $135.00 new
Magpul BUIS - $80.00 new
AAC Brakeout - $80.00 new
Slashes heavy buffer designed for gas piston rifles - $145.00 new

Also included
8 magazines worth (160 rounds) Federal Gold Medal Match 168 Grain - $224.00
2 magazines worth (40 rounds) Hornady Amax 168 Grain - $60.00
Additional pistons (2) to tune the rifle to the load you are shooting, similar to having an adjustable gas block on a DI rifle.

So as you can see, this is truly optics ready.  I've included a picture of my last 5 round string at 100m, and called the flyer that can be seen.  Without that one flyer, this is shooting at, or just under 1 MOA.  It is also worth mentioning this was shot in rubber mulch, on a bipod with a sand sock under the rear stock, not in a cradle or sled.

I have put only federal gold medal match 168 and 175 grain, and hornady steel case 155 grain match ammo through this rifle


Round count is at 540 rounds down range.

Not including the ammunition, the total cost was ~$3280.00, I'm asking $2600.00 for everything minus the ammunition, including the ammo will bring you up to $2850.00

There are a few dings on the rifle from use,  so I've chosen what I consider to be a fair price for the rifle, I doubt I'll be lowering it much, but I will entertain reasonable offers.

I'm looking for 5.56 rifles, ammo and such plus cash or additional firearms to meet close to the asking price.  Will reduce overall cost by a few hundred for trades provided the trade offers are good.  I'm really interested in the following:

IWI Tavor (FDE preferred, but black can work too)
Bushmaster ACR (again FDE preferred)
PWS 5.56 rifles
Any others you might have please let me know

Also interested in
FNX Tactical 45 (FDE)

Please don't bother emailing me asking if I'll take a price, and when I reply with either a midway price, or in one case lower the price by removing certain upgrades to meet your price, not reply to my return email, that's messed up, quite frankly.  Don't bother emailing me a price if you don't have the money to back it up, window shop elsewhere on the internet, not here.

Thanks for your time

postcontent:
CASH ONLY/NO TRADES/NO LOWBALLERS!

There are 25 more pictures of this rifle at this link   http://imgur.com/a/GBs2b  http://imgur.com/a/GBs2b  

Springfield Armory M1 Garand 30-06 plus ammo Up for sale is this Korean War Era M1 Garand with nearly new Boyd's stock set. Stock set has all new metal except for the butt plate. Has a few dings and some scratches on the right side of the butt stock. There is also one scratch. This gun was inspected nuzzle to butt stock, and then some, by a former CMP armorer with intimate knowledge of these Garands . All parts were checked out to specs and all that was replaced was the Op-Rod Spring and follower/slide assembly.

Shoots great  least out to 100 yards on his personal range with everything grouping nicely on official CMP Targets http://www . midwayusa .com/product/792024/ nra -official-high-power-rifle-target- sr -1-100-yard-slow-and-rapid-fire-paper-package-of-10 0 

Since I took it out of the wood, you'll have to take it out and re-sight it to get it broken in and restore some of the accuracy lost. Speaking of sights, I've had aftermarket National Match sights installed to include the special ring that goes between the sight base grooves and the elevation knob. This allows more minute clicks when adjusting the elevation. The front sight came with a cross hairs so I figure what the hell and put those in as well. There is also a National Match Op-Rod made by Remington Arms under contract with the original Springfield Armory back in the late 50s to early 60s. There is no rust on this gun and the  Dec 1953 barrel's bore is bright and shiny with no pitting. Muzzle wear gages at less than 2 and throat erosion at less than 2 as well. Basically it's a brand new barrel which is great for accuracy.

I'm also including 48 rounds of HXP Greek surplus 30-06 on Enbloc clips in a vintage bandoleer. If you have any questions, please email me.

title: For Sale:  Ruger 1022 Tapco Tactical Trainer AR15 Clone
location: Clayton, NC, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
I am selling this Ruger 1022 AR15 Clone with all of the accessories. So there is no confusion, there are two prices for the rifle (One with the red dot $420 and one without $350). The rifle is in excellent condition and only has one spot where the finish has been scratched. It is on the magazine release lever where my thumb nail has scratched it over the years. I built this rifle a few years ago for three gun competition training and it holds very similar to an AR15. It has had numerous upgrades in the trigger system, barrel, sights and furniture that I will list below. I am not asking new gun and accessories prices for this rifle but am going to list the original prices that I paid so you can see what you are buying.

Even though the condition of the rifle is excellent and shoots flawlessly, it has been used. If you want all of the accessories, including the new Red Dot, I am asking $420 for the entire package. If you do not want the red dot I am asking $350 for the rifle, fore end grips and magazines and I will keep the red dot. 

I live in the Clayton area but travel for a living so I can meet anywhere in Central/Eastern NC if you’d like. If you have any questions about the function of the rifle I would recommend meeting at a range of your choice. I am happy to let you shoot the rifle so you can see this thing is the real deal AR clone and functions perfectly. I will provide the ammo if you like or you can bring your own. It runs on anything. If you buy the rifle I will also throw in another 100 rounds so you can have a little fun. 

In the past I have had offers to break up the parts and have not done that. I feel that it is a complete set and would like to keep it that way. However, as long as you are not requesting just the barrel or something that would make it non-functioning, I will split up the package. So if you do not want the entire package as it is listed just let me know what you would like and we can settle on a price.

I will follow all laws and will not sell this rifle without a carry conceal permit or an FFL transfer.

Here are the options for this rifle:

•	TAPCO TACTICAL TRAINER STOCK: This stock is different than the regular Tapco takedown stock as it has the front rail over the barrel and takes both the .920” bull barrel and regular Ruger barrel. It has the SAW style pistol grip and two butt stocks. One is an angled stock tube for low profile sights and sits more like a traditional rifle (which is pictured) and the other is a straight stock tube that is appropriate for more “AR” height sights such as the Eotech or Aimpoint. Both are adjustable just like the AR15 standard collapsible stock. The stock also includes a sling adapter that will accept the HK style hooks. This stock currently sells for $114 on the Tapco site and slightly less on Amazon.
•	HOGUE .920” BULL BARREL: I put the heavier bull barrel on this rifle to give it more weight to the front so it would hold more like an AR. What surprised me the most what the accuracy increase I got with it. While zeroing the sight I had on it at the time I decided to see how far it would shoot with CCI MiniMag ammo. I consistently hit a paint can at 200 yards with every shot out of the rifle with zero magnification. It is impressive. Hogue no longer makes this barrel but similar barrels sell from $149 to $249.
•	BUSHNELL TRS-25 RED DOT SIGHT: I purchased this sight just a year ago when I had planned on turning the rifle back into a standard .22. The sight has only the rounds in it that I shot to zero it and is the newest part of this rig. It has multiple brightness settings and gives a pretty clean sight picture. They currently sell for $90 and if you do not want this sight I will be more than happy to keep it as it will sit on just about any platform.
•	RUGER BX-25 MAGAZINES: I have three Ruger BX-25 magazines that come with this rifle. They are factory made Ruger products and are pretty impressive. They hold 25 rounds each and have steel feed lips. I have been quite impressed with them as they have not had a single feed failure since I purchased them. The older Butler Creek ones did as the plastic feed lips just… well… sucked. I am including all three of these and three Ruger 10 round rotary magazines.
•	TAPCO FORE END GRIPS: I purchased two Tapco vertical grips to keep the look consistent with the Tapco stock. One is a stubby grip and the other is the same style but longer and comes with a bipod extension. They both have rubber bottoms and storage capacity. The stubby one still sells for $21 and the longer one with the bipod extension sells for $35.
•	ERGO RAIL COVERS: I purchased rail covers for the entire fore end so they would not tear my hands up. They are Ergo and sell for $10 each.
•	TRIGGER UPGRADE: I bought a complete set of springs, hammer and trigger for this rifle to clean up the gravely feel of the standard Ruger trigger. For the life of me I can’t remember the name of the company as it was years ago when I installed it and there is no value I can put to it. However, I thought it appropriate to mention since the trigger is not factory. I did not lighten the trigger much as I wanted it to mimic the AR trigger in my Stag but it is a very clean crisp pull. Much better than the original factory work.
•	HOGUE OVER MOLDED STOCK: I have a second stock for this rifle that I will throw in if you buy it. It is a Hogue over molded rubber stock. It has the lines of a traditional rifle stock and can be switched by just unscrewing the main screw of the rifle, pulling out the action and placing it in the new stock. This sold for $99 new and is in good condition. It has marks on the stock where I had a bag attached to the butt for a cheek rest but still works fine. I am just throwing this in as a bonus if you buy the rifle.

If you look at just the accessories you are getting a good deal. All are in like new condition and together with the rifle make a pretty awesome package. Thanks for looking and pleas let me know if there are any questions.

title: For Sale:  HECKLER & KOCH P7M8 ***H&K P7M8
postcontent:
Heckler & Koch P7M8 is the perfect auto-loading police-use pistol. The reason it is considered ideal is due to its completely unique safety system, namely the "squeezecocker" control surface built into the front of the grip. When the operator picks up the firearm, the main shooting hand instinctually squeezes the panel rearward, and this action cocks the striker rearward while unlocking the sear for use. The panel is spring-loaded, which means when pressure is reduced, it snaps forward, decocking the striker and locking the trigger. This system is also designed to release the slide when it is locked rearward. This design eliminates the need for a decocker, external safety lever or slide stop lever, making the sides of the firearm completely flush and reducing overall width. The barrel is fixed (does not cant upwards) which means despite the firearm's compact size, it is capable of printing groups of 2 inches or less at 25 yards. This accuracy is easily comparable to many high-end automatic pistols in production. It has classic three white-dot sights dovetailed into the slide. I purchased it New in 1996 and have fired approximately 400 rounds through it without a single jam.Will include extra mags and nice holster.OREGON Residents ONLY
ONLY TRADE FOR FN 5 7 Five Seven

title: For Sale:  HECKLER & KOCH P7M8 ***H&K P7M8
postcontent:
Heckler & Koch P7M8 is the perfect auto-loading police-use pistol. The reason it is considered ideal is due to its completely unique safety system, namely the "squeezecocker" control surface built into the front of the grip. When the operator picks up the firearm, the main shooting hand instinctually squeezes the panel rearward, and this action cocks the striker rearward while unlocking the sear for use. The panel is spring-loaded, which means when pressure is reduced, it snaps forward, decocking the striker and locking the trigger. This system is also designed to release the slide when it is locked rearward. This design eliminates the need for a decocker, external safety lever or slide stop lever, making the sides of the firearm completely flush and reducing overall width. The barrel is fixed (does not cant upwards) which means despite the firearm's compact size, it is capable of printing groups of 2 inches or less at 25 yards. This accuracy is easily comparable to many high-end automatic pistols in production. It has classic three white-dot sights dovetailed into the slide. I purchased it New in 1996 and have fired approximately 400 rounds through it without a single jam.Will include extra mags and nice holster.OREGON Residents ONLY
ONLY TRADE FOR FN 5 7 Five Seven
